Exif.Name: Camera Make
Exif.Description: Manufacturer of the digital still camera (DSC), scanner, video digitizer or other equipment that generated the image. When this is left blank, it is treated as unknown

Exif.Name: Camera Model
Exif.Description: Model name or number of the digital still camera (DSC), scanner, video digitizer or other equipment that generated the image. When this is left blank, it is treated as unknown

Exif.Name: Horizontal Resolution
Exif.Description: Number of pixels per ResolutionUnit

Exif.Name: Vertical Resolution
Exif.Description: Number of pixels per ResolutionUnit

Exif.Name: Resolution Unit
Exif.Description: Unit for measuring Horizontal and Vertical resolutions

Exif.Name: Software
Exif.Description: Records the name and version of the software or firmware of the camera or image input device used to generate the image

Exif.Name: Date Time
Exif.Description: Date and time of image creation or when last modified

Exif.Name: YCbCr Positioning
Exif.Description: Position of chrominance components in relation to the luminance component

Exif.Name: Compression
Exif.Description: Compression scheme used for the image data

Exif.Description: Number of pixels per ResolutionUnit

Exif.Description: Offset to the start byte of the JPEG compressed thumbnail data

Exif.Description: Number of bytes of JPEG compressed thumbnail data

Exif.Name: Exposure Time
Exif.Description: Exposure time in seconds

Exif.Name: F Number
Exif.Description: Camera F number

Exif.Name: Exposure Program

Exif.Name: ISO Speed Ratings
Exif.Description: Indicates the ISO Speed and ISO Latitude of the camera or input device as specified in ISO 12232

Exif.Name: Photo Exif Version

Exif.Description: Date and time when the original image data was generated

Exif.Description: Records date and time when the image was stored as digital data

Exif.Description: Records the valid width of the meaningful image when it has been compressed

Exif.Description: Records the valid height of the meaningful image when it has been compressed

Exif.Name: Photo File Source

Exif.Description: Indicates the use of special processing on image data; such as rendering geared to output

Exif.Name: Photo Exposure Mode

Exif.Description: Indicates the digital zoom ratio when the image was shot; 0 indeicates that Digital Zoom was not used

Exif.Name: Photo Focal Length In 35mm Film
Exif.Description: Indicates the equivalent focal length, assuming a 35mm film camera, in mm

Exif.Name: Photo Gain Control
Exif.Description: Indicates the degree of overall image gain adjustment

Exif.Name: Photo Contrast
Exif.Description: Indicates the direction of contrast processing applied by the camera when the image was shot

Exif.Name: Photo Saturation
Exif.Description: Indicates the direction of saturation processing applied by the camera when the image was shot

Exif.Name: Photo Sharpness
Exif.Description: Indicates the direction of sharpness processing applied by the camera when the image was shot

Exif.Name: Photo Subject Distance Range
Exif.Description: Indicates the distance to the subject

Gps.Name: GPS Latitude Reference
Gps.Description: Indicates whether the latitude is North or South latitude

Gps.Name: GPS Latitude
Gps.Description: Indicates the latitude as three Rational values giving the degress, minutes and seconds respectively

Gps.Name: GPS Longitude Reference
Gps.Description: Indicates whether the longitude is East or West longitude

Gps.Name: GPS Longitude
Gps.Description: Indicates the longitude as three Rational values giving the degress, minutes and seconds respectively

Gps.StringValue: GPS Altitude Reference = 0 (Altitude above sea level)
Gps.Name: GPS Altitude Reference
Gps.Description: Indicates the altitude reference used for the GPSAltitude value

Gps.Name: GPS TimeStamp
Gps.Description: Indicates the UTC time expressed as three Rational values giving the hour, minute and second

Gps.Name: GPS Satellites
Gps.Description: Indicates the GPS satellites used for measurements; the tag can be used to describe the number of satellites, their ID number, angle of elevation, azimuth, SNR and other information

Gps.Name: GPS Image Direction Reference
Gps.Description: Indicates the reference for giving the direction of the image when it is captured

Gps.Name: GPS Map Datum
Gps.Description: Indicates the geodetic survey data used by the GPS receiver

Gps.Name: GPS Date Stamp
Gps.Description: Recording date and time information relative to UTC (Coordinated Universal Time)
